  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003E.agda" type="external">erct-003E.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A,B \colon   \mathsf {PathObj}</tex> be two <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path objects</link>. The <em><strong>binary product</strong></em> <tex>A \times  B</tex> is equipped with the structure of a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> by setting <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( x,y \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{A \times  B} \mathopen {} \left ( u,v \right ) \mathclose {} : \equiv  x \cong _{A}u  \times  y \cong _{B}v</tex> and <tex>1_{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \right ) \mathclose {} }  : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {refl} , \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
 
   
   
 
